      <h2>Building &amp; Rebuilding in Lahaina</h2>
      <p>Lahaina has always been a community of resilience. For generations, this historic West Maui town was the center of Hawaiian culture, the capital of the Kingdom of Hawaii, and later one of Maui's most distinctive places — a blend of history, commerce, and community that couldn't be found anywhere else on the island.</p>

      <p>The August 2023 wildfires changed Lahaina profoundly. The destruction of large parts of the historic town is a loss that the entire community of Maui shares. But Lahaina is being rebuilt, and that rebuilding process represents one of the most significant construction efforts in Hawaii's modern history. Property owners, families, and the broader West Maui community are in various stages of assessment, planning, permitting, and reconstruction.</p>

      <p>Great General LLC is available to help with that process. Whether you're rebuilding a property affected by the fires, renovating a home that survived, working on a property in the broader West Maui area, or undertaking a commercial renovation in Lahaina's recovering commercial district, we bring a licensed, accountable general contractor to your project.</p>

      <h2>West Maui Residential Construction</h2>
      <p>Beyond the historic downtown, Lahaina's broader district encompasses a wide range of residential communities — the neighborhoods of Launiupoko, Puamana, Olowalu, and the areas climbing up toward Lahainaluna Road and the hills above town. These neighborhoods include both older homes that reflect Lahaina's plantation heritage and newer developments built to serve West Maui's growing residential demand.</p>

      <p>We work throughout this residential landscape. Kitchen and bathroom remodels, interior renovations, structural repairs, custom carpentry, and metal fabrication for gates, railings, and fencing — all of it is available to Lahaina-area homeowners through Great General LLC. We hold the Hawaii DCCA B License that authorizes us to self-perform carpentry, framing, drywall, and demolition work, which means we bring a full contracting capability to West Maui projects without adding subcontractor layers.</p>

      <h2>Ka'anapali and North West Maui</h2>
      <p>North of Lahaina proper, the Ka'anapali resort strip and the communities extending toward Kapalua and Napili represent a distinct segment of West Maui's construction market. Ka'anapali's resort properties — the Westin, Royal Lahaina, Kaanapali Alii, and the dozens of condominium resorts along Kaanapali Parkway — include some of West Maui's most active renovation markets.</p>

      <p>Vacation rental renovation in Ka'anapali and Napili follows patterns similar to Wailea and Kihei: unit owners renovating between rental seasons, property managers coordinating upgrades across multiple units, and individual condo owners modernizing their investment to stay competitive in the vacation rental market. We handle all of this — including HOA coordination, scheduling around rental calendars, and managing the logistics of renovation work in multi-story resort buildings.</p>

      <h2>Historic Preservation Considerations</h2>
      <p>Lahaina's historic character — including the surviving pre-fire portions of the town and properties on the State and National Historic Registers — creates specific construction considerations. Work on or near historically significant properties may trigger additional review requirements beyond standard Maui County permitting. We're familiar with Hawaii's historic preservation framework and factor these requirements into project planning from the beginning.</p>

      <h2>General Contracting Services in Lahaina</h2>
      <p>Our full range of contractor services is available throughout Lahaina, Ka'anapali, Napili, Kapalua, and West Maui:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>General contracting and project management</strong> — full scope coordination including Maui County permits, construction sequencing, and inspection management for West Maui projects of all types.</li>
        <li><strong>Residential renovation</strong> — kitchen remodels, bathroom renovations, interior framing and buildouts, flooring, drywall, and custom carpentry for Lahaina-area homes.</li>
        <li><strong>Vacation rental renovation</strong> — unit upgrades, full unit remodels, and multi-unit renovation programs for Ka'anapali, Napili, and Lahaina-area vacation rental properties.</li>
        <li><strong>Custom metal fabrication</strong> — gates, railings, fencing, and architectural metalwork for West Maui properties. Coastal-grade material specifications for oceanfront and high-exposure installations.</li>
        <li><strong>Commercial renovation</strong> — tenant improvements and commercial buildouts for Lahaina-area businesses as the commercial district rebuilds and recovers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Navigating Maui County Permits in West Maui</h2>
      <p>Permitting for construction projects in West Maui goes through Maui County's Department of Public Works. For properties in or near the fire-affected zones, there are additional considerations and processes that apply during the rebuilding period. We work through the county permitting process regularly and will handle permit applications, plan reviews, and inspection scheduling as part of our general contracting scope for your Lahaina project.</p>

      <h2>Free On-Site Estimates in Lahaina and West Maui</h2>
      <p>We come to you anywhere in West Maui — Lahaina, Ka'anapali, Napili, Kapalua, Launiupoko, Olowalu, and the surrounding communities. Free on-site estimate, written scope, no obligation. Call (808) 795-4044 or submit an estimate request online.</p>

      <h2>Supporting the West Maui Community</h2>
      <p>Maui is our home. The rebuilding of Lahaina is a community effort that will take years, and contractors have a real role to play in it — doing work with integrity, pulling proper permits, using quality materials, and treating property owners fairly. That's the standard Great General LLC holds itself to, in Lahaina and everywhere else on the island.</p>
